cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.NE 

This paper deals with the robustness of image classifiers, specifically on the ImageNet dataset. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also discusses the use of deep learning techniques and architectures, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the vulnerabilities of current classifiers, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also mentions the need for future research, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
